                                            Implementing a Linked List
                                        </h2>
                                        <p class="s-post-text">
                                            A Linked List is essentially a set of objects that use a common Link class. Each Link object contains a reference to the next Link object in the chain. This reference is stored in a field called “next.”

                                            In the example below, the “next” field in the Link object maintains an object reference. A reference is a number that refers to an object’s address in a computer’s memory. Regardless of the object, the reference will be the same size in memory.
